<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
To attach a file to a page you should: 
    <ol type="1">

    <li>
<p>
<a href="http://mlton.org/Preferences"><img src="moin-www.png" alt="[WWW]" height="11" width="11">Create an account</a> and login. 
</p>
</li>
    <li class="gap">
<p>
Click on the <tt>AttachFile</tt> link at the bottom of the page to  which you wish to attach the file. 
</p>
</li>
    <li class="gap">
<p>
Enter the file name in the "<tt>File&nbsp;to&nbsp;upload</tt>" box and click  <tt>upload</tt>. 
</p>
</li>

    </ol>


<p>
Once you have done this, you can refer to the file on the page using the <tt>attachment:filename</tt> wiki syntax. 
</p>
<p>
Here is an <a href="http://mlton.org/pages/HowToAttachFile/attachments/example"><img src="moin-www.png" alt="[WWW]" height="11" width="11">example</a>. 
</p>
</div>



